      "body" : "I agree with @practicalswift that we should stay close to unix style as much as possible. I've seen interfaces of the form `cmd help sumbcommand` and `cmd subcommand --help`. I'm not sure if those are unix philosophies but I think there's precedent there. \r\n\r\n@laanwj what do you perceive as the risk of this extra complexity? I'm still new to the community and am trying to understand how risk/reward tradeoffs are thought about. I understand that this PR adds more complexity but I don't see the complexity as high risk. ",
